item.title: Richard Fox
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Richard is John's younger brother, which may come as a suprise considering they look like twins. They have remained close throughout the years and have a mutual agreement to keep it that way until further notice. One time, as small children, John flipped a go-cart over on Lane's arm and made him swear not to tell, but Lane is over it, he swears. In 2017, Lane will make fun of John for actually participating in writing a groomsman bio about him, and the wedding website as a whole.
item.excerpt:encoded: Richard and Quinten met in college when they lived in the same neighborhood. Quinten's girlfriend, at the time, had a chihuahua that preferred to hangout in our backyard rather than his.

item.title: Albert Gibson
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Albert Gibson is the younger brother of the bride, Ashley. Jason, having grown up with two sisters and no brother, is extremely excited to add John to the family and balance out the female/male ratio! Over the past six years of John and Ashley's relationship, Jason has taken John's side in arguments much more often than Ashley's. You have earned a seat at the table.
item.excerpt:encoded: Albert Gibson and Chris met in college through mutual friends. Their similar personalities and humor made them instant friends and it stayed that way throughout the rest of college and still is today.

item.title: Bobby Allen
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Bobby Allen and Chase have been family friends for as long they can remember. Although John ends up wrestling with him in the front yard every time Chase visits and forces him to do manual labor in 100 degree south Georgia heat, he has still agreed to take part in the wedding... Thanks Chase.
item.excerpt:encoded: Bobby Allen and Chase have been family friends for as long they can remember. Although John ends up wrestling with him in the front yard every time.

item.title: Craig Cooper
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Craig Cooper and Quinten met in college when they lived in the same neighborhood. Quinten's girlfriend, at the time, had a chihuahua that preferred to hangout in our backyard rather than his. After a few trips to retrieve his girlfriend's dog, John and Quinten became friends. Note: Quinten is no longer with that girlfriend, does not have a chihauahua and is recently engaged! We couldn't imagine getting married without you Quintina!
item.excerpt:encoded: Craig is the younger brother of the bride, Ashley. Jason, having grown up with two sisters and no brother, is extremely excited to add John to the family and balance out the female/male ratio.

item.title: Sandra Crawford
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Sierra and I met in Augusta, GA through work when we were still in high school. She is literally one of the funniest people I know. All we do is laugh when were together, even when we're in the middle of a haunted tour and they are talking about someone's untimely death.... true story. Even though John and Sierra have a love-hate relationship because he likes to instigate and encourage Sierra to make poor choices she has still agreed to be a bridesmaid (thank goodness...)! Can't wait for her to stand by my side on my big day!
item.excerpt:encoded: Jessica and I met in Augusta, GA, where we both lived, and immediately clicked! We both ended up going to Georgia Southern University where we got even closer and became the twisted sisters.

item.title: Maria Cruz
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Maria and I met at Georgia Southern through mutual friends and happened to live in the same neighborhood. She is just as goofy as I am and is always down to have a good time! She is so incredibly fun to be around and is one of the most understanding people I know! I could not have made it through college without our late night drives, bonfires, Gnats, and being able to just show up at her house unannounced with no explanation what-so-ever. I can't wait to go through this crazy experience with her by my side!
item.excerpt:encoded: Maria and I met through work and instantly bonded over our shared passion for Snapchat filters, Starbucks, and talking about coworker's current 'lady friends' in order to avoid actually doing any real work.

item.title: Samantha Gomez
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Jessica and I met in Augusta, GA, where we both lived, and immediately clicked! We both ended up going to Georgia Southern University where we got even closer and became the twisted sisters (where my Grey's Anatomy fans at??)! We have been able to experience so much of our lives together and I am so excited we get to add my wedding to the list! Could not imagine getting married without this lifelong friend standing by my side!
item.excerpt:encoded: It may be 'expected' that a bride picks her sister to be her MOH, but the truth is, I would have picked Kristi to be my MOH even if she was not! She is so much fun to be around and is one of the funniest people I know.

item.title: Lori Jacobs
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: It may be 'expected' that a bride picks her sister to be her MOH, but the truth is, I would have picked Lori to be my MOH even if she was not! She is so much fun to be around and is one of the funniest people I know! Also, when picking a MOH, it is important to not only pick your best friend but to pick someone who will beat up anyone who may make you mad on your wedding day. She has stood by me through everything else in life and now I can't wait for her to stand by my side while I marry the man of my dreams!
item.excerpt:encoded: Lori and I met at Georgia Southern through mutual friends and happened to live in the same neighborhood. She is just as goofy as I am and is always down to have a good time! She is so incredibly fun to be around and is one of the most understanding people.

item.title: Engagement
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
We have the same creative vision, we see things very differently and thus we always shoot together our approaches compliment each other and help in weaving a complete story. One of us is always with the bride & the other with the groom leading our respective team members so we are able to do full justice in documenting the parallel stories happening across both families.
To sum up, we want your wedding pictures & films to feel real, so that the natural magic of your story is preserved. And when your family from the next generation takes a look at this story, they get a true sense of who you are and what happened on your big day.

Who We Are

We are driven to help our clients wedding to be succeed by providing better solution.

Since 2009

Ceremony Wedding Planners is a full service Wedding Planning company founded in 2009 and based in Bangalore, India. We have the joy of helping families realize their vision of a wedding.

View More

Our History

Ceremony ~ Wedding Planners has become synonymous with the words wedding planning and find themselves to be the first and one of the best Wedding planners in Los Vegas.

View More

Get Registered

To get registered your wedding with us you can leave a message about your wedding event using our contact form.








    Our Planning Includes

    We are glad to provide these services for your wedding with perfect planning.

    FLOWER DECORATIONS

    Choosing what each bloom really means can make your decision a little easier.

    BEST RESTAURANT

    Eat, drink, and be married at your favorite neighborhood joint.

    WEDDING CAKE

    A wedding cake is the traditional cake served at wedding receptions.

    PHOTOSHOOT

    An occasion when a photographer takes a series of photographs.

    COSTUMES

    A wedding dress is the clothing worn by a bride during a wedding ceremony.

    HONEYMOON

    Vacation taken by newlyweds immediately after their wedding.

    Client Says

    There was absolutely no way we were going ahead in the planning of our wedding without theirs professionalism.

    Robert Jones

    Event Manager

    You are the main glue that makes everything go well for the wedding day & Our wedding day turned out beautifully.

    Carl Phillips

    Event Organizer

    We are so very thankful to have had the privilege of working with the perfect planning in our memorable day.

    Angela Young

    Creative Lead

    A massive Thank you to The ceremony everyone said it was the best wedding and your staff were all a great bunch of people.

    Gerald Freeman

    Planner

    Showcase your wedding photos in a memorable fashion with this handcrafted gallery.

item.title: Wedding Ceremony
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
We believe that real moments have the extraordinary power to carry the legacy of a couple across generations, and our style is about looking for those moments of truth and capturing them in an honest manner. We try to be as unobtrusive as possible and approach weddings like observers, similar to how we approach our street photography & documentary filmmaking work, some which can be seen here.
We are constantly experimenting with a mix of photojournalism, portraiture and documentary filmmaking, while adding our own twist which comes from who we are as people, and the things we notice as photographers & filmmakers.

item.title: Wedding Reception
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
While we have the same creative vision, we see things very differently and thus we always shoot together our approaches compliment each other and help in weaving a complete story. One of us is always with the bride & the other with the groom leading our respective team members so we are able to do full justice in documenting the parallel stories happening across both families.
We are constantly experimenting with a mix of photojournalism, portraiture and documentary filmmaking, while adding our own twist which comes from who we are as people, and the things we notice as photographers & filmmakers.

item.title: Pre-wedding
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
We have the same creative vision, we see things very differently and thus we always shoot together - our approaches compliment each other and help in weaving a complete story. One of us is always with the bride & the other with the groom leading our respective team members - so we are able to do full justice in documenting the parallel stories happening across both families.
To sum up, we want your wedding pictures & films to feel real, so that the natural magic of your story is preserved. And when your family from the next generation takes a look at this story, they get a true sense of who you are and what happened on your big day.

item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Suggested text: Our website address is: https://victorthemes.com/themes/ceremony.

Comments

Suggested text: When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

Suggested text: If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Cookies

Suggested text: If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Suggested text: Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Who we share your data with

Suggested text: If you request a password reset, your IP address will be included in the reset email.

How long we retain your data

Suggested text: If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

Suggested text: If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where your data is sent

Suggested text: Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

item.title: Refund and Returns Policy
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This is a sample page.

Overview

Our refund and returns policy lasts 30 days. If 30 days have passed since your purchase, we cant offer you a full refund or exchange.

To be eligible for a return, your item must be unused and in the same condition that you received it. It must also be in the original packaging.

Several types of goods are exempt from being returned. Perishable goods such as food, flowers, newspapers or magazines cannot be returned. We also do not accept products that are intimate or sanitary goods, hazardous materials, or flammable liquids or gases.

Additional non-returnable items:

  • Gift cards
  • Downloadable software products
  • Some health and personal care items

To complete your return, we require a receipt or proof of purchase.

Please do not send your purchase back to the manufacturer.

There are certain situations where only partial refunds are granted:

  • Book with obvious signs of use
  • CD, DVD, VHS tape, software, video game, cassette tape, or vinyl record that has been opened.
  • Any item not in its original condition, is damaged or missing parts for reasons not due to our error.
  • Any item that is returned more than 30 days after delivery

Refunds

Once your return is received and inspected, we will send you an email to notify you that we have received your returned item. We will also notify you of the approval or rejection of your refund.

If you are approved, then your refund will be processed, and a credit will automatically be applied to your credit card or original method of payment, within a certain amount of days.

Late or missing refunds

If you havent received a refund yet, first check your bank account again.

Then contact your credit card company, it may take some time before your refund is officially posted.

Next contact your bank. There is often some processing time before a refund is posted.

If youve done all of this and you still have not received your refund yet, please contact us at {email address}.

Sale items

Only regular priced items may be refunded. Sale items cannot be refunded.

Exchanges

We only replace items if they are defective or damaged. If you need to exchange it for the same item, send us an email at {email address} and send your item to: {physical address}.

Gifts

If the item was marked as a gift when purchased and shipped directly to you, youll receive a gift credit for the value of your return. Once the returned item is received, a gift certificate will be mailed to you.

If the item wasnt marked as a gift when purchased, or the gift giver had the order shipped to themselves to give to you later, we will send a refund to the gift giver and they will find out about your return.

Shipping returns

To return your product, you should mail your product to: {physical address}.

You will be responsible for paying for your own shipping costs for returning your item. Shipping costs are non-refundable. If you receive a refund, the cost of return shipping will be deducted from your refund.

Depending on where you live, the time it may take for your exchanged product to reach you may vary.

If you are returning more expensive items, you may consider using a trackable shipping service or purchasing shipping insurance. We dont guarantee that we will receive your returned item.

Need help?

Contact us at {email} for questions related to refunds and returns.

Who We Are

We are driven to help our clients wedding to be succeed by providing better solution.

Since 2009

Ceremony Wedding Planners is a full service Wedding Planning company founded in 2009 and based in Bangalore, India. We have the joy of helping families realize their vision of a wedding.

View More

Our History

Ceremony ~ Wedding Planners has become synonymous with the words wedding planning and find themselves to be the first and one of the best Wedding planners in Los Vegas.

View More

Get Registered

To get registered your wedding with us you can leave a message about your wedding event using our contact form.

    Choosing what each bloom really means can make your decision a little easier.

    Eat, drink, and be married at your favorite neighborhood joint.

    WEDDING CAKE

    A wedding cake is the traditional cake served at wedding receptions.

    PHOTOSHOOT

    An occasion when a photographer takes a series of photographs.

    COSTUMES

    A wedding dress is the clothing worn by a bride during a wedding ceremony.

    HONEYMOON

    Vacation taken by newlyweds immediately after their wedding.

item.title: Our Story
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Story Of Love

When you find the one person you can't live without. your soul mate that thinks of you and only you. When you are talking to each other, you say the same thing without knowing it.

Daniel Taylor

28.04.1990

We met through a mutual friend at the end of our freshman year in college at Georgia. I noticed her beautiful eyes, and how outgoing she was.

Cheryl Spencer

06.10.1994

We did meet through a mutual friend at the end of our freshman year in college at Georgia Southern. We got along really well and clicked instantly.

RSVP NOW

Our Proposal Story

Discover our proposal story from how we met initially and fall in love with each other.

First Meet At College

We started dating in highschool. I had the hugest crush on him at 21, my stomach would do flips every time I saw him. It all started when he asked me what color my prom dress was so he could match his tie.

How He Asked?

They were with her whole family and he kept trying to get her outside. She just wanted to play with her nephews and didn't know what he was up to. Meanwhile her whole family was in on it.

Will You Marry Me Cheryl?

We went for a weekend vacation. We were together on the beach, and when I saw the ring, I immediately started crying. He looked at me all confused. 'Why are you crying?' He asked softly will you marry me cheryl?.

She Hug Him & Said yes!

We were skiing in Breckenridge. We were at the top of the mountain and he bent down to fix his binding. I was rolling my eyes because I just wanted to get going when all of a sudden he looked up at me with the ring

Photography

To buy something exceptional, Mindset must be relentlessly focused on the smallest things in wedding related items.

item.title: Guestbook
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Write Us For Something

Your heartfelt words more meaning to us in the occasion of our wedding please write some thoughts and word for us.




People Wrote For Us

We spent a lot of time perfecting the schedule, and making sure everything was perfect, and it really was the perfect day!

Helen Henry

Photographer

I will always remember my wedding day to be absolutely perfect, and Fidan and Carly were a big part of creating that perfect memory.

Rose Barnes

Creative Head

Beautiful venue with caring, helpful staff. We were happy to use silver birches for our rehearsal and the cottages, too. The food was delicious, bartenders were fun, and the price seemed too good to be true.

Philip Hansen

Decor Head

We recently had our Wedding reception at The ceremony Hotel and it was beyond amazing. Our entire family also stayed in the hotel for the weekend and they couldnt fault the hotel or the staff. Christina, Mick and the whole team were fantastic and everything came together nicely.

Charles Sullivan

Art Director

Thank you both for your superb work, we are truly amazed by our wedding photos. The photos are absolutely beautiful, you managed to capture our special day moment by moment. Every time we look at the images we are reminded of the emotion, the laughs and fun of the day.

Christine Green

Stage Designer

A massive Thank you to The ceremony everyone said it was the best wedding and your staff were all a great bunch of people.

Gerald Freeman

Planner

We are so very thankful to have had the privilege of working with the perfect planning in our memorable day.

Angela Young

Creative Lead

You are the main glue that makes everything go well for the wedding day & Our wedding day turned out beautifully.

Carl Phillips

Event Organizer

There was absolutely no way we were going ahead in the planning of our wedding without theirs professionalism.

Robert Jones

Event Manager

Save The Date

Carlson & Shirley

Save The Date

Robert & Rebecca

Save The Date

Samuel & Cheryl

05.04.2019 - Studio 23, Peter Loop, OJ

Story Of Love

When you find the one person you can't live without. your soul mate that thinks of you and only you. When you are talking to each other, you say the same thing without knowing it.

Daniel Taylor

28.04.1990

We met through a mutual friend at the end of our freshman year in college at Georgia. I noticed her beautiful eyes, and how outgoing she was.

Cheryl Spencer

06.10.1994

We did meet through a mutual friend at the end of our freshman year in college at Georgia Southern. We got along really well and clicked instantly.

28.08.2019

Venue at Lucy Forks, Patriciafur, United States.

RSVP NOW

We Are Getting Married

Remaining days for our wedding ceremony, We are expecting all of your presence.

Remaining days for our Wedding ceremony

The Wedding Day

Our wedding day event order as follows with different cultures and religions will incorporate other elements or swap things around, but if you're planning to create a ceremony.

Main Ceremony

13.08.2019

Marriage

09.30am onwards

The processional begins with the grandparents, flows through the parents, groom, officiant, wedding party, flower girl, and ring bearer, and ends with the bride making her entrance.

Words of Welcome

12.30pm onwards

Once everyone is in place, the officiant will say a few words of welcome. He or she may thank guests for bearing witness to your union, as well as welcome everyone to your venue and your celebration.

Photography

2.00pm onwards

the officiant will offer an introduction and some thoughts on marriage. This could be a brief recounting of your love story, words on what marriage means to you, or a statement about the ceremony to come and represents.

Wedding Cake

3.30pm onwards

A wedding cake is the traditional cake served at wedding receptions following dinner.The wedding cake is served at a wedding breakfast; the 'wedding breakfast' does not mean the meal will be held in the morning.

Wedding Party

4.00pm onwards

At the wedding party the officiant introduces the married couple for the first time. Then, the bride and groom lead the recessional back up the aisle as guests shower you with the rice!

Photography

A good snapshot at your wedding can stops a moment from running away.

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)

...or something like this:

The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.

As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Bachelor Party
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Ceremony Weddings & Events team has built a reputation over the last 15 years in business in Los Angles, as the Best Wedding and Event planners and producers in USA. We have also been named several times as one of the Top Event Planners in the Country and named top wedding planner in Los Angles. We are a genuine and passionate group of planners who adore what we do. We offer unsurpassed service and unequaled events by staying true to our passion of collaboration with our clients to tell their stories with ease, beauty, artistry and style. Our designs are sophisticated, elegant, detail-oriented, playful, inspired, unique and cohesive.
Were trendsetters, style-setters, rule makers and even rule breakers. Were incredibly inspired by YOU and telling YOUR story. We don't believe in pretension, anything "cookie-cutter" or stuffy parties. We are driven by constant exploration through travel, art, fashion and nature. We laugh a lot and love celebrating the journey with you. We never say no and always think of our clients first and make the impossible possible.
Learn more about each of our talented planners by clicking on each image below. Our planners are creative, imaginative, resourceful and above all else, dreamers. We all dream of the details to tell your story. Renny is the owner and works on full-service Corporate Events, and larger scale full-service tented weddings locally and around the world. She has planned thousands of weddings over her career of 25 years. Jack is our Senior Planner and Lead Designer with over 18 years experience in design and planning. He focuses on full-service Design, Planning and Production for larger scale local weddings and destination weddings. He specializes in highly technical logistics and imaginative details including tented estate weddings and highly specialized requests.
Our philosophy is one which advocates personalisation, attention to detail and a seamless wedding planning process. Over the past 10 years, we have established ourselves as a premium wedding planning company and work together with some of the most talented wedding suppliers in the industry. We pride ourselves in delivering top class service together with an exceptional product.
Jack and Turner are our Associate planners with over 10 years planning experience. They provide partial planning and full-service planning on local mid-scale weddings at Hotels, Lofts, and Museums, and weddings in Wisconsin and Michigan.

We are a genuine and passionate group of planners who adore what we do. We offer unsurpassed service and unequaled events by staying true to our passion of collaboration with our clients to tell their stories with ease, beauty, artistry and style. Our designs are sophisticated, elegant, detail-oriented, playful, inspired, unique and cohesive.
Were trendsetters, style-setters, rule makers and even rule breakers. Were incredibly inspired by YOU and telling YOUR story. We don't believe in pretension, anything "cookie-cutter" or stuffy parties. We are driven by constant exploration through travel, art, fashion and nature. We laugh a lot and love celebrating the journey with you. We never say no and always think of our clients first and make the impossible possible.
Learn more about each of our talented planners by clicking on each image below. Our planners are creative, imaginative, resourceful and above all else, dreamers. We all dream of the details to tell your story. Renny is the owner and works on full-service Corporate Events, and larger scale full-service tented weddings locally and around the world. She has planned thousands of weddings over her career of 25 years. Jack is our Senior Planner and Lead Designer with over 18 years experience in design and planning. He focuses on full-service Design, Planning and Production for larger scale local weddings and destination weddings. He specializes in highly technical logistics and imaginative details including tented estate weddings and highly specialized requests.
Our philosophy is one which advocates personalisation, attention to detail and a seamless wedding planning process. Over the past 10 years, we have established ourselves as a premium wedding planning company and work together with some of the most talented wedding suppliers in the industry. We pride ourselves in delivering top class service together with an exceptional product.
Jack and Turner are our Associate planners with over 10 years planning experience. They provide partial planning and full-service planning on local mid-scale weddings at Hotels, Lofts, and Museums, and weddings in Wisconsin and Michigan.

item.title: Rose Barnes

item.title: Philip Hansen
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Beautiful venue with caring, helpful staff. We were happy to use silver birches for our rehearsal and the cottages, too. The food was delicious, bartenders were fun, and the price seemed too good to be true.

item.title: Charles Sullivan
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: We recently had our Wedding reception at The ceremony Hotel and it was beyond amazing. Our entire family also stayed in the hotel for the weekend and they couldnt fault the hotel or the staff. Christina, Mick and the whole team were fantastic and everything came together nicely.

item.title: Christine Green
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Thank you both for your superb work, we are truly amazed by our wedding photos. The photos are absolutely beautiful, you managed to capture our special day moment by moment. Every time we look at the images we are reminded of the emotion, the laughs and fun of the day.
